    },
    "body": "Some kernel paths read the current time (e.g. header validation's future-time check, and the `btck_SynchronizationState` carried by `btck_NotifyBlockTip` / `btck_NotifyHeaderTip` callbacks), which makes them awkward to exercise deterministically in tests. This PR exposes `btck_set_mock_time` as a wrapper over the existing `SetMockTime`, mirroring what the node has via the `setmocktime` RPC.\r\n\r\nPrior IRC discussion: https://gnusha.org/bitcoin-kernel/2026-06-04.log\r\n",
